HEADWORD: Tripodian
<hw>Tri*po"di*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>
<def>An ancient stringed instrument; -- so called because, in form, it
resembled the Delphic tripod.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

